# WeCom Audit Workflow

This document covers the end-to-end workflow, scheduled execution model, and the change log from the latest refactoring.

Entry points:

- `Invoke-WeComAuditScheduler.ps1` (scheduled entry — date calculation + orchestration)
- `Invoke-AuditLog.ps1` (pure data analysis)
- `Invoke-AuditValidate.ps1` (backup validation + archive + source cleanup)

---

## 1. Scheduled Execution Model

The pipeline runs as **two Windows Task Scheduler jobs** per cycle, every 2 weeks on Thursday. An ops window between the two jobs allows manual file placement (miniapp screenshots, upload confirmation, etc.) before validation.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    S1[Job 1: Thursday 08:00] --> W1[Invoke-WeComAuditScheduler.ps1 -Phase Analysis]
    W1 --> A1[Read ScheduleAnchor from config]
    A1 --> A2[Compute cycleIndex from anchor to today]
    A2 --> A3{cycleIndex % 2}
    A3 -- even --> V2[CurrentRunWeeks = 2]
    A3 -- odd --> V4[CurrentRunWeeks = 4]
    V2 --> P1[Phase 1: Invoke-AuditLog.ps1]
    V4 --> P1
    P1 --> P1C{Analysis exit code}
    P1C -- 0 --> RID[Read RunId from latest-run.json]
    RID --> OUT[Output RunId + exit 0]
    P1C -- non-zero --> FAIL1[Abort, exit with analysis code]

    S2[Job 2: Thursday 16:00] --> W2[Invoke-WeComAuditScheduler.ps1 -Phase Validate]
    W2 --> R1[Read RunId from latest-run.json]
    R1 --> R2{RunId found + dates match?}
    R2 -- No --> FAIL2[Abort: no valid RunId]
    R2 -- Yes --> P2[Phase 2: Invoke-AuditValidate.ps1 -RunId X -CurrentRunWeeks N]
    P2 --> DONE[Exit with validation code]

    OPS[Ops window 08:00 ~ 16:00] -.->|copy miniapp screenshots,<br/>upload confirmation, etc.| BF[Backup folder]
```

### Ops Window

Between Job 1 and Job 2, the ops team manually copies files to the backup folder (`{BackupRoot}/{endDate}/`). These files are **not** produced by the analysis phase — they are external artifacts required for validation:

| File | Applies to |
|---|---|
| `msms-miniapp.png` | 4-week |
| `msbic-miniapp.png` | 4-week |
| `Conduct WeCom Log Audit file uploaded.msg` | 4-week |
| Member operation records `.xlsx` | 2-week and 4-week |

Both 2-week and 4-week cycles require this ops window.

### Biweekly Schedule Example

| Date | Cycle | Job 1 (08:00) | Ops Window | Job 2 (16:00) |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 2026-04-02 (Thu) | 0 (even) | analysis | copy files | 2-week validate + archive |
| 2026-04-16 (Thu) | 1 (odd) | analysis | copy files | 4-week validate + archive |
| 2026-04-30 (Thu) | 2 (even) | analysis | copy files | 2-week validate + archive |
| 2026-05-14 (Thu) | 3 (odd) | analysis | copy files | 4-week validate + archive |

### Date Calculation

`ScheduleAnchor` is the **first scheduled run date** (a Thursday), which equals the first `endDate`. The job runs on `endDate` and analyzes the previous 2 weeks.

```
ScheduleAnchor = config (must be a Thursday, e.g. '20260402')
cycleIndex     = floor((today - anchor).Days / 14)
endDate        = anchor + (cycleIndex * 14)    -- = today on a cycle Thursday
startDate      = endDate - 14
```

`-StartDate` parameter overrides auto-calculation for manual/catch-up runs. Note: `-StartDate` only overrides the date range — `CurrentRunWeeks` is still derived from today's `cycleIndex`, not the overridden dates. Use `-ForceCurrentRunWeeks` when backfilling historical cycles.

### `-Phase` Parameter

| Value | Behavior |
|---|---|
| `Analysis` | Run Phase 1 only. Read and output RunId after success. Used by Job 1. |
| `Validate` | Run Phase 2 only. Read RunId from `latest-run.json`, verify date consistency, call validate with `-RunId`. Used by Job 2 or manual trigger. |
| `All` | Run Phase 1 then Phase 2 sequentially (no ops window). For development/testing only — **not recommended for production**. |

