## 4. Validation + Archive Flow (`Invoke-AuditValidate.ps1`)

Validates backup folder completeness, then archives source files and deletes originals.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Start: Invoke-AuditValidate.ps1] --> B[Load config + BackupValidationRules]
    B --> BA[Resolve-SourceCleanupConfig + Assert-SourceCleanupConfig]
    BA --> C[Resolve backup folder]
    C --> D{Summary source}
    D -->|RunId| D2[Resolve from runs/RunId]
    D -->|AnalysisSummaryPath| D1[Use provided path]
    D -->|DateRange| D3[Auto-discover latest matching]
    D -->|LatestRun| D4[Read latest-run.json]

    D1 --> E[Load analysis summary + task summaries]
    D2 --> E
    D3 --> E
    D4 --> E

    E --> G[Determine CurrentRunWeeks: param > summary > config > default]
    G --> H[Find related runs, merge dynamic task summaries]
    H --> I[Build expected file list based on CurrentRunWeeks]
    I --> J[Test-BackupFolderContent: expected vs actual]
    J --> K{Validation passed?}

    K -- No --> L[Write summary, exit 1]

    K -- Yes --> M[Extract source file paths from analysis summary]
    M --> N{Source files to archive?}

    N -- No --> O1[ArchiveStatus = NoSourceFiles, exit 0]

    N -- Yes --> P[Copy source files to backup folder with hash dedup]
    P --> Q{Copy succeeded?}
    Q -- No --> R[ArchiveStatus = BackupFailed, exit 2]
    Q -- Yes --> S[Invoke-SourceFileCleanup: 4-layer safety check + delete]
    S --> T{Cleanup result}
    T -- Aborted --> U1[ArchiveStatus = CleanupAborted, exit 2]
    T -- PartiallyFailed --> U2[ArchiveStatus = CleanupPartiallyFailed, exit 2]
    T -- Success --> U3[ArchiveStatus = Success, exit 0]
```

### 2-Week vs 4-Week Validation

Both trigger backup + delete on success. The difference is the expected file list:

| File Category | 2-Week | 4-Week |
|---|---|---|
| `CommonFixedFiles` | Yes | Yes |
| `DynamicFiles` (conditional on task summary) | Yes | Yes |
| `TwoWeekFixedFiles` (source CSVs, member records) | Yes | -- |
| `FourWeekFixedFiles` (miniapp screenshots, upload confirmation, extended records) | -- | Yes |

### Archive Phase — Deletion Safeguards

Source file deletion (via `Invoke-SourceFileCleanup`) runs the following checks before removing each file:

| Check | Function | What it prevents |
|---|---|---|
| Path normalization | `Get-NormalizedFullPath` | `..` traversal or inconsistent path formats affecting prefix match |
| Whitelist | `Test-PathWithinAllowedRoots` | Deletion of any file outside configured `AllowedRoots` (fail-closed) |
| Reparse point rejection | `Test-SafeToDeleteSourceFile` | Symlink/junction following into unintended directories |
| Hash verification | SHA256 compare | Deleting a source file whose backup copy doesn't match |

Additional pre-checks:
- Backup folder must contain at least as many files as unique pending deletions
- Shared-source tasks are deduplicated at entry (no double-delete)

#### Design weight assessment

The current operating context is ~3 files per cycle on a fixed NAS path, biweekly. The safeguards above were designed conservatively. A proportionality analysis:

| Check | Runtime cost | Practical value in current context | Verdict |
|---|---|---|---|
| Path normalization | Negligible | Low — all paths come from config templates, no user input | Keep (zero cost, harmless) |
| **Whitelist** | Negligible | **High — core protection**, already caught a real config mismatch | **Essential** |
| Reparse point | Negligible | Very low — enterprise NAS CIFS shares rarely have symlinks | Keep (zero cost), but could downgrade to warning in future |
| **Hash verification** | ~1s for 3 files | Medium — guards against silent copy corruption on network storage | **Keep as safety net** |

The startup assertion (`Assert-SourceCleanupConfig`) adds ~50 lines and runs once. It has already caught the QA config path-type mismatch (local InputRoot vs UNC AllowedRoots). It is justified as a config validation function, not as a security boundary.

**Overall**: the safeguard set is heavier than the operating context strictly requires, but the execution cost is negligible (~1s total for 3 files). The real cost is cognitive — readers may overestimate the complexity or risk level of the deletion operation. Documentation should present these as straightforward deletion pre-checks, not as a layered security architecture.

### Exit Codes

| Code | Meaning |
|---|---|
| 0 | Validation passed, archive succeeded (or no source files) |
| 1 | Validation failed (expected files missing) |
| 2 | Validation passed but archive had issues (backup copy failed, cleanup aborted/partial) |

### Validation Artifacts

```
runs\<RunId>\validation\
  backup-validation.log
  backup-folder-validation.json
  backup-folder-validation.txt
  backup-validation-summary.json   # includes ArchiveStatus + ArchiveResult
```

