## 7. Configuration (`analysis_task.config.psd1`)

```powershell
@{
    ScheduleAnchor = '20260402'           # Biweekly anchor (first run date, must be Thursday)
    ExecutionMode = 'FailFast'            # or 'ContinueOnError'
    CurrentRunWeeks = '2'                 # default; overridden by scheduler
    InputRoot = 'C:\addin_deploy_cert'    # NAS source root (local mount or UNC)
    LogRoot = 'C:\SysAdmin\log'           # local log root
    BackupRoot = '\\cod.test.com.cn\apptest\wecom_audit_log_backup'

    SourceCleanup = @{
        Enabled      = $true
        AllowedRoots = @('\\cod.test.com.cn\apptest\wecom_audit_log')
    }

    BackupValidationRules = @{ ... }
    Tasks = @( ... )
}
```

### Path Consistency Requirement

`InputRoot` and `SourceCleanup.AllowedRoots` must use the **same path type** (both local or both UNC). `Assert-SourceCleanupConfig` verifies at startup that every enabled task's resolved `InputDirectory` falls within an allowed root — this check uses path prefix matching, so `C:\local\path` will never match `\\server\share\path` even if they point to the same NAS folder.

### Priority Chains

| Concern | Parameter | Env Var | Config Key | Fallback |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Log/output root | `-OutputRoot` | `WECOM_AUDIT_LOG_ROOT` | `LogRoot` | config dir |
| Backup root | `-BackupFolder` (validate) | `WECOM_AUDIT_BACKUP_ROOT` | `BackupRoot` | output root |
| Source input root | -- | `WECOM_AUDIT_INPUT_ROOT` | `InputRoot` | `C:\addin_deploy_cert` |
| Config path | `-ConfigPath` | `WECOM_AUDIT_CONFIG_PATH` | -- | `analysis_task.config.psd1` |

